{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ab1f88f-1f4a-4b7b-baea-c446c8954d63","content":"The directory is empty — there's no project yet. No worries, here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes this a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Tells `dotnet pack` to produce a tool package |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users invoke (e.g. `my-mcp-server`) |\n| `OutputType` must be `Exe` | Tools must be executables |\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nThat's the minimum configuration. Want me to scaffold the project for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"53fd972a-589a-4d0a-8025-93eec0466c91","outputTokens":510,"requestId":"D01A:299D5F:14D7BB8:175C99D:6A0674A6"},"id":"70d83fd0-55d6-4b68-a133-b9a2500f379f","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:19:45.530Z","parentId":"41314a0a-843b-4477-9dcd-95a04c0ff12a"}
